lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAnna Lobanova, East West University.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJoshua Davis, &lt;em&gt;Assistant Director for Transfer Admission&lt;/em&gt;, Concordia University Chicago&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJohn Clayton, &lt;em&gt;Dean of Admissions&lt;/em&gt;, Newman University&lt;br /&gt;\r\nRobert Melaragni, &lt;em&gt;Dean of Admissions&lt;/em&gt;, Fisher College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLarry Jensen, &lt;em&gt;Director of Admission&lt;/em&gt;, Christchurch School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMichelle Fairbank, &lt;em&gt;Vice-President of Admissions&lt;/em&gt;, Thomas More Prep - Marian High School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMichelle Huntsman-Tessers, Wasatch Academy&lt;br /&gt;\r\nCathy Sankey, &lt;em&gt;Principal&lt;/em&gt;, Dublin Jerome High School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMark Powers, Thornton Academy&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJeff Lemke, &lt;em&gt;Admissions Director&lt;/em&gt;, St. Croix Schools&lt;br /&gt;\r\nYvonne Martel, &lt;em&gt;Director of Undergraduate Admissions&lt;/em&gt;, Jacksonville University&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJulie Poland Middleton, &lt;em&gt;Associate Director of Admission&lt;/em&gt;, Hebron Academy&lt;br /&gt;\r\nRuby Canning, Foxcroft Academy&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJames Lewis, &lt;em&gt;Director of International Admissions &amp;amp; Recruiting&lt;/em&gt;, Kansas State University&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSarka Nastalkova, &lt;em&gt;Senior Assistant Director of Admissions&lt;/em&gt;, Iona College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nCaleb Black, &lt;em&gt;International Admission Counselor&lt;/em&gt;, Milwaukee School of Engineering&lt;br /&gt;\r\nJenna Davis, &lt;em&gt;Director of International Admission&lt;/em&gt;, George School&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AUSTRALIA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Ben Waymire, Trinity College - The University of Melbourne&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLynn Tan, &lt;em&gt;Regional Marketing Manager, International Office&lt;/em&gt;, Curtin University&lt;br /&gt;\r\nIris Pang, &lt;em&gt;International Registrar&lt;/em&gt;, The Knox School&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE UNITED KINGDOM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Simon Dooley, &lt;em&gt;International Marketing Manager&lt;/em&gt;, Chichester College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSarah Hicklin, Oswestry School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAyelen Arias, &lt;em&gt;Clerical Assistant, International Office&lt;/em&gt;, Aston University&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NEW ZEALAND&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Leigh Riley, Nelson College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nKerry Finnigan, &lt;em&gt;Director of International Students&lt;/em&gt;, Onslow School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nMichele Mc Cathy, Gisbone boy''s high school&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWendy Kirkwood, Gisbone girl''s high school&lt;br /&gt;\r\nDianna Murdoch, Waimea College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSally Rax, Director of International students, Glenfield College&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAlison Stephenson, International Students Manager, Otago girl''s high school&lt;br /&gt;\r\nTania Woodham, Cashmere high school&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SINGAPORE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Madeline May Suan Phua, ST. Francis Methodist School&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLim Shini, Singapore University of Technology and Design&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 5, 1),
(72, 'The Lifestyle', '&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;The United States of America originated in a revolution which separated it from the British Crown. The constitution, drafted in 1787, established a federal system with a division of powers which has remained unchanged in form since its inception. The United States has an advanced industrial economy that is highly mechanized. The gross national product is the largest in the world. The country more than meets its own economic needs and is the world''s leading exporter of food. USA is also the country with diverse cultures and is the home for extensive groups of ethics, customs and values.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Especially, for the students looking for the best overseas education and planning to put their careers on the fast track, USA is the hottest destination. This is because it has immense range of specialties, high quality of education, great opportunities, which attract students from different countries of the world.&amp;nbsp; Students can choose a suitable university from over 3800 universities and colleges available in USA that facilitate several educational programs. The U.S. provides a lot of offers for international students like prestigious education in the world, assorted cities and towns, dazzling natural parks, different events and multicultural population.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facts and figures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Full name:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; The &lt;/strong&gt;United States of America&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Location: &lt;/strong&gt;The mainland United States borders Canada to the north and Mexico, the Gulf of Mexico, and the Straits of Florida to the south. The western border meets the Pacific Ocean, and to the east lies the Atlantic Ocean.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;- Total area:&lt;/strong&gt; 9,631,420 km2 (world''s fourth-largest country after Russia, China and Canada)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Population (2010 est.):&lt;/strong&gt; 310,232,863 (growth rate: 0.9%); birth rate: 13.8/1000; infant mortality rate: 6.1/1000; life expectancy: 78.2; density per sq mi: 85&lt;br /&gt;\r\n- &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.infoplease.com/cgi-bin/id/A0855603&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Capital:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Washington DC&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Largest cities:&lt;/strong&gt; New York; Los Angeles, Chicago, Houston, Philadelphia, Phoenix, San Diego, San Antonio, Dallas, Detroit&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Monetary unit:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;U.S dollar&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Official language:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;English&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Major religion:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Christianity&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Climate:&lt;/strong&gt; mostly temperate, but tropical in Hawaii and Florida, arctic in Alaska, semiarid in the great plains west of the Mississippi River, and arid in the Great Basin of the southwest;&amp;nbsp; low winter temperatures in the northwest are ameliorated occasionally in January and February by warm Chinook winds from the eastern slopes of the Rocky Mountains.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;File:US map - states.png&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;422&quot; src=&quot;http://sn.edu.vn/images/map-us.gif&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;624&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Terrain:&lt;/strong&gt; vast central plain, mountains in west, hills and low mountains in east; rugged mountains and broad river valleys in Alaska; rugged, volcanic topography in Hawaii.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;strong&gt;- Transportation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;buses and trains is the most popular mode of transportation in the United States. Besides, there are many other transports including: ferries, electric buses and subways, taxis, bicycles, cars etc…&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture and American lifestyle&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;The US contains a highly diverse population, the product of numerous and sustained waves of immigration. Ethnic and racial diversity – the “melting pot” – is celebrated as a core element of the American ideology&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; The people in the United States tend to the human values and socioeconomic triumph. The people and culture in the United States are much different from Indians. The students who choose the universities will come across the regional culture and rich traditions and customs. The nation has a multi-racial society that merges new immigrants despite of the country from which they come from. The culture of the USA reveals a trend to hybridize pop culture, thus it is called as high culture. The expansion of the American culture was apparent in many aspects like, music, dance, movies, sports, architecture, literature, poetry, cuisine and visual arts, which are highly followed by all around the world.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Traditional American cuisine arts are much similar to several Western countries. Wheat is the primary cereal grain. The main ingredients in American food include turkey, potatoes, sweet potatoes, corn, slow-cooked pork and beef barbecue, crab cakes, potato chips, and cookies. Food snacks such as, fried chicken, pizzas, hamburgers, hot dogs, apple pie are derived from the recipes of various immigrants. Usually Americans prefer coffee to tea and milk is the chronic breakfast drink. With the evolution of beverage industries, orange juice and sweetened soft drinks are highly consumed.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;As you may know, one of the hallmarks of U.S. culture is independence. In order to make friends, you must take the initiative to meet people. Because of the American value of independence, Americans will not always be looking out for you, or making sure that you are getting acquainted with other people. They assume you are taking care of yourself unless you tell them differently. If you don''t ask for help, Americans will assume you don''t need anything. So remember: ask for help when you need it!&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 6, 1);
