(74, 'WHATCOM COMMUNITY COLLEGE', '&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;296&quot; src=&quot;http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8341/8262262549_de50f3ea60_b.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;737&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Whatcom Comminuty college is a public, two- year college which is accredited by the Northwest Commission on colleges and Universities, with programs of study that are approved by the Washington State Board for Community and Technical Colleges. Whatcom offters associate degrees in unversity transfer, general studies, and professional/ technical programs, as well as certificate programs in professional/ technical areas. Whatcom also provides English as a second Language (ESL) instruction to prepare students for college- level coursework.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Whatcom operates on an academic quarter system with four starting dates which allow students to begin their studies in the fall, winter, spring or summer quarters. With an average class size of 30 students or less, whatcom is committed to offering personalized instrution for every students.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;An average of 7,000 students students study at Whatcom each quarter, including more than 150 international students from over 30 countries.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Whatcom employs approximately 250 full and part-time faculty, 90% of whom hold Doctorate or Masters degrees in their repective fields.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Transfer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Whatcom’s most popular course of study is the university transfer program, which prepares students to transfer to universities across the US. The Associate in Arts and Science degree is designed for students who plan to transfer to a four – year university to complete their bachelor’s degree. With the assistance of International Program staff, many whatcom graduates transfer each year to universities in Washington State and throughout the US.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;WCC international students have been accepted at:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color