mal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 7, 1),
(78, 'WORCESTER ACADEMY', '&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;353&quot; src=&quot;http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8346/8250737315_aea271954e_b.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;746&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Worcester Academy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Worcester Academy is a private, independent, co-ed day and boarding school for grades 6 to 12 and postgraduates in Worcester, Massachusetts.&amp;nbsp; Its historic urban setting, diverse community, and challenging curriculum provide students with a solid, real-world education.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nVisit Worcester Academy and you''ll find motivated students and exceptional teachers engaged in dynamic, experiential learning.&amp;nbsp; It challenge assumptions and collaborate in search of a greater understanding of its world.&amp;nbsp; Worcester Academy’s &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.worcesteracademy.org/academics/middleschool&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;Middle School&lt;/a&gt;utilizes an interdisciplinary curriculum that teaches students how to think critically, logically, and analytically.&amp;nbsp; Its &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/academics/UpperSchool&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;high school&lt;/a&gt;curriculum includes over 30 Honors and AP courses, 5 language choices (including Mandarin), 42 arts offerings and a math program that is recognized throughout New England for its rigor.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nStudents gain global perspective through opportunities that extend beyond the classroom and use 21st-century tools, like their 1-to-1 assigned MacBooks, to enhance their learning and self-expression.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWorcester Academy has been cultivating academic excellence and shaping future leaders since 1834.&amp;nbsp; JoiningWorcester Academy to learn more about how it prepares students to &quot;Achieve the Honorable.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;546&quot; src=&quot;http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8343/8251805588_05882972ca_b.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;819&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 26px;&quot;&gt;Tuition &amp;amp; Fees&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; width: 871px;&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Fees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			US Applications -- $60 non-refundable&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			International Applications -- $125 US non-refundable&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;2012-2013 TUITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			Worcester Academy tuition includes a personalized, challenging &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/academics?&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot; title=&quot;Academics&quot;&gt;academic experience&lt;/a&gt;that includes small class sizes taught by superior teachers, a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/academics/information_services&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot; title=&quot;1-to-1 Laptop Program&quot;&gt;school issued Macbook&lt;/a&gt;stocked with current software valued at $5000, access to private music lessons, academic support services, personalized &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/academics/college_counseling&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot; title=&quot;College Counseling&quot;&gt;college counseling&lt;/a&gt;for juniors and seniors, along with conveniences like meals, athletic uniform laundering and seasonal athletic equipment storage.&amp;nbsp; Best of all, both students and parents will gain life-long friendships and membership in the WA community, and a unique global educational experience that will set your student on the path to academic success.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Day Students&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			(includes lunch)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			Middle School (Grades 6-8) -- $26,980&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			Upper School (Grades 9-12) -- $29,190&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Boarding Students&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			(includes all meals)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			5-Day Boarders (Grades 9-PG only) -- $42,490&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			7-Day Boarders (Grades 9-PG only) -- $51,400&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Tuition Refund Plan (TRP)&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp; 1%&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Technology Fee&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			(all students)&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			$500&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			For most families, investing in an independent school education requires careful financial planning and consideration. To begin the process, you should start by discussing options with your &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/admission/contact&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot; title=&quot;Admission Contacts&quot;&gt;admission counselor&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The 2011-2012 financial aid budget of $4.6 million reflects Worcester Academy''s commitment to supporting students from a broad range of economic situations. Worcester Academy offers financial aid to students with demonstrated need.&amp;nbsp; In fact, 38% of the student body received financial aid in 2011.&amp;nbsp; You may find that you qualify for a financial award, which may be supplemented with loans or a combination of payment plans.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Since each family is unique, families applying for aid are encouraged to review our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.worcesteracademy.org/admission/financial-aid&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot; title=&quot;Financial Aid&quot;&gt;financial aid information&lt;/a&gt;and schedule a conversation with our Director of Financial Aid.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			Tuition does not meet the actual cost of educating a Worcester Academy student.&amp;nbsp; The difference is made up by the Academy''s endowment funds and gifts.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Payment Schedules&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			You may arrange to pay tuition with a ten or nine-month installment plan offered thru &lt;a href=&quot;https://online.factsmgt.com/Tmg/public/AgreementSignup.aspx?t=3JNJ4&amp;amp;siv=y&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot;FACTS Tuition Pay Plan&quot;&gt;FACTS Tuition Pay Plan&lt;/a&gt;; tuition can also be paid in full at one time, or in two installments with a firstpayment of 75 percent of the balance due August 1st followed by a second payment of 25 percent December 15th. Specific information on the several payment plans is available from the Admission Office.&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;br /&gt;\r\n			&lt;strong&gt;Other Charges and Expenses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p&gt;·&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;International Student Fee&lt;/strong&gt; -- $3,570 U.S., drawn from U.S. banks only&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n			&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; height=&quot;542&quot; src=&quot;http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8494/8263249520_9d50d9994a_b.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;723&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n		&lt;/tr&gt;\r\n	&lt;/tbody&gt;\r\n&lt;/table&gt;\r\n', 9, 1);
