 normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Each student grows into him or herself because of the care extended by full time Residential Life Faculty and an environment for him or her to learn, mature, and find his or her own way of doing things and learning. Our Residential Life Faculty strives to prepare a student for life at college, providing opportunities to develop personally, socially, and academically, while still exercising personal freedom and accountability, under supervision with appropriate boundaries. Living on this campus amongst Wasatch faculty and students in an intimate, unique community, allows a student to find his or her identity, develop talents, enjoy an extended family and establish friendships for life.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dorm dormitory&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Students&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nAlice&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&am