one; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;The ALCI welcomes new&amp;nbsp;international students, transfer students from other schools in&amp;nbsp;the U.S., students&amp;nbsp;with undergraduate or graduate conditional admission to CSU San Marcos, and semester abroad students.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;To apply, send a complete application and required documents to the ALCI.&amp;nbsp; We will send you an I-20 after we process your application.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; We strongly recommend that you apply at least 2 months before the program start date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Housing Options&amp;nbsp;for ALCI Students&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;As a new ALCI student, you must make your housing arrangements before you leave your home country.&amp;nbsp; You must confirm your homestay, on campus apartment, or other housing before you arrive in San Marcos.&amp;nbsp; The ALCI Office cannot reserve housing for you.&amp;nbsp; Read the housing information below and click on the headings for more information about each kind of housing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.csusm.edu/alci/housing/homestay.html&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homestay with Local Families&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nWith this choice, you will live near campus with an American host family. Homestay includes breakfast and dinner, a bedroom (with a&amp;nbsp;bed and a desk), a closet, a shared or private bathroom, and laundry facilities.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Homestay fees are $650 - $700 per month depending on the agency.&amp;nbsp; Each agency also charges a non-refundable application fee. A private homestay agency will place you with a family.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;-&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.csusm.edu/housing&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campus Housing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;University Village Apartments and the new Quad at San Marcos are modern apartments designed exclusively for students attending California State University San Marcos. If you will attend ALCI for one complete semester or a full academic year, you can apply to live in campus housing.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Private or shared bedrooms&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; A kitchen&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; A furnished living area&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Furnished rooms&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Air-conditioning&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-left: 28.5pt;&quot;&gt;·&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; All utilities (local telephone, high-speed internet, and cable TV)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cost for 2011-2012 academic year&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(August -May)&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPrivate Bedroom: $9500&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLarge Shared Bedroom: $8500&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSmall Shared Bedroom: $6750&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cost for Fall 2011 or Spring 2012 semester&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;\r\nPrivate Bedroom: $4750&lt;br /&gt;\r\nLarge Shared Bedroom: $4250&lt;br /&gt;\r\nSmall Shared Bedroom: $3375&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Meals are not included.&amp;nbsp; Students must bring their own bed linens (or rent them for&amp;nbsp;a fee), appliances, kitchen items, etc.&amp;nbsp; UVA is managed by a professional staff, which provides student activities, 24-hour student services, and quality maintenance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;- &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.csusm.edu/alci/housing/off_campus_housing.html&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Off-campus Apartments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;The local area offers many reasonably priced apartments.&amp;nbsp; Students who want to live off campus are responsible for finding their own housing.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp; Off-Campus Housing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;The San Marcos, Carlsbad, Escondido, Oceanside, and Vista communities near CSU San Marcos offer many reasonably priced apartments. Rents are about:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;Studio apartments: $700-$850+ per month.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nOne-bedroom apartments: $800 - $1,100+ per month.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nTwo-bedroom apartments: $1,100-$1,300+ per month.&lt;br /&gt;\r\nThree-bedroom apartments: $1,300-$1,600+ per month.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;If you choose to live off-campus, you are responsible for finding your own housing. We recommend that students visit the apartment or home in person before signing a lease or paying any money.&amp;nbsp; Often, it can be difficult to arrange for an off-campus apartment from your home country. Because of this, most students choose homestay during their first semester at the ALCI.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n', 17, 1);
INSERT INTO `news_description` (`id`, `title`, `content`, `news_id`, `language_id`) VALUES
(96, 'HILLSBOROUGH COMMUNITY COLLEGE', '&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8480/8251811208_2d2c22ae28_b.jpg&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px; width: 1024px; height: 246px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About HCC&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;HCC supports its international student with programs and services from start to finish – from admission and US entry, all the way through your two years of study at HCC, With support for transferring to a four _year US university. HCC makes sure you have everything you nedd to get the very best education.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;HCC is a fully accredited, public community college in the metropolitan region of Tampa, Florida. Since 1968, It has been providing a high-quality, contemporary education to a large and diverse domestic and international community. It helps more 47,000 students – including 2,600 students from 134 different countries – take advantage of its vast course offering across its five campus locations. In addition to educating approximately 160 F-1 international students from 54 nations, the College enrolls more than 2,600 permanent U.S. residents who are citizens of&amp;nbsp;146 different countries.&amp;nbsp; Matching its cultural diversity, the College offers more than 150 degree, career and university transfer programs.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;HCC is proud of its role in helping its students gain employment or transfer to four-year Universities throughout the United States.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Choose HCC?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Lower tuition cost&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Affordable, new&amp;nbsp;housing on campus&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Personalized, quality instruction&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Small class sizes&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Five safe, convenient campus locations&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Easy transfer to a four-year university&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Intensive English instruction&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Tutoring and academic assistance&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Academic, athletic, environmental, and cultural organizations&lt;/li&gt;\r\n	&lt;li&gt;Accreditation by Southern Association of Colleges and Schools&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;University Transfer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;For international students who intend to earn a Bachelor’s degree or higher&amp;nbsp;in the United States, HCC is a great place to start!&amp;nbsp; The College provides a general studies, or liberal arts curriculum, which qualifies students to transfer as a third-year student to a four-year college or university.&amp;nbsp; After earning an Associate&amp;nbsp;in Arts (AA) degree at HCC, students may transfer to one of Florida''s 11 public universities, or to other &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hccfl.edu/media/715678/university%20transfer%20listing.pdf&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); text-decoration: none;&quot;&gt;four-year colleges and universities throughout the United States&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;table align=&quot;left&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(117, 117, 117); font-family: ''Times New Roman'', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; width: 753px;&quot; width=&quot;753&quot;&gt;\r\n	&lt;tbody&gt;\r\n		&lt;tr&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;Hillsborough&amp;nbsp;Community College&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td rowspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td&gt;\r\n			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;U.S. College or University&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n			&lt;td rowspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;\r\n			&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;=&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n			&lt;/td&gt;\r\n	